<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Foundations targeted in pursuit of Pounds
1.3bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BRONWEN MADDOX
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The pursuit of Pounds 1.3bn missing from the late Mr Robert Maxwell's public
companies has homed in on six secretive Liechtenstein foundations and two
Swiss companies, writes Bronwen Maddox.
The six foundations or 'stiftungs' - Corry, Allandra, Baccano, Akim, Kiara,
and Jungo - have been targeted by accountants Arthur Andersen and
liquidators of the collapsed Maxwell empire in their search for the missing
millions.
Most of the missing money appears to have flowed out from the public
companies Maxwell Communication Corporation and Mirror Group Newspapers and
their pension funds to the web of 400 private Maxwell companies - and then
out again to Liechtenstein, Switzerland, the US and Panama.
Arthur Andersen, who are administrators of the private companies under UK
insolvency laws, now suspect that some of these foundations were used to
conceal the origin of funds.
The Swiss-based companies Yakosa Finanzierungs and Servex are thought likely
to have had a central role in the alleged scheme in which Mr Maxwell
illegally supported the share price of MCC, now the subject of an
investigation by the Serious Fraud Office.
</TEXT>
