FT  15 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Greycoat temporarily loses chief through
illness
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER, Property Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GREYCOAT is losing the services of Mr Geoffrey Wilson, its founder and
executive chairman, for a number of months following successful heart
by-pass surgery on Monday.
The property company's share price has been under pressure in the past
fortnight due to rumours that the company was likely to break its banking
covenants and that it would not be able to refinance its Embankment Place
office block in the bond market. During that time the price has nearly
halved.
Mr Wilson will take some months to recover from the operation, which was not
preceded by any illness.
Analysts expect that Mr Richard Guignard, finance director, will take charge
in Mr Wilson's absence. The issue will be decided by a board meeting at the
end of the week.
It is also likely that the company will consider a permanent split between
the roles of chairman and chief executive.
The company has denied that it has breached it covenants. It said that its
Embankment Place bond issue, which is being handled by Dumas West, is
progressing smoothly and is likely to be signed at the end of the month.
