secretary, that Mr Major was 'grubbing around for a photo opportunity' was
insulting.
Mr Robin Squire (C Hornchurch) said the prospect of a dictatorship or
irresponsible country acquiring any of the 27,000 nuclear weapons previously
controlled by the Soviet Union was 'terrifying'.
