FT  15 JAN 92 / Takeover Panel chief will be ally of industry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MRS FRANCES HEATON, the first woman to be appointed director-general of the
Takeover Panel, said yesterday she intended to give more weight to the views
of industrial and commercial companies.
Mrs Heaton, a corporate finance director of investment bankers Lazard
Brothers, will take over as director-general on March 11.
She said one of her main objectives was to ensure that all interested groups
were involved in the formulation of views on takeover policy. That would
involve 'not just the practitioners, who are the intermediaries, but also
their clients'. She added: 'There has been quite a heavy weighting on the
City side of the panel in the past.'
The panel had already moved to represent industry's views better by
providing for the appointment of three senior industry figures to advise it,
she said.
Mrs Heaton, 47, who joined Lazards in 1980 after a 10-year career at the
Treasury, has advised on privatisations while with the bank. She has also
advised property groups including London and Edinburgh Trust and the group
seeking to develop London's County Hall. Her experience of contested
takeovers includes Hanson's bid for London Brick and TSB's for Hogg
Robinson.
