<DATELINE>
   KINSHASA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
About 200 delegates walked out of Zaire's national conference on political
reform yesterday, saying representation was too heavily weighted towards the
opposition, Reuter reports from Kinshasa.
Last week, hundreds of delegates loyal to authoritarian President Mobutu
Sese Seko withdrew from the conference for the same reason. The latest
walkout was by delegates from the southern Shaba region.
The conference, called to chart a democratic future for Zaire, officially
opened in August, but has been suspended much of the time and has
accomplished virtually nothing.
