<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Police confiscated 4m litres of wine in northern Italy yesterday and
arrested four men in an alleged doctoring scandal, Reuter reports from
Milan.
Paramilitary police said the wine was being analysed but had probably been
laced with toxic substances in cellars near the northern towns of Vicenza
and Padova.
Italy, one of the world's largest wine exporters, was hit by a scandal six
years ago in which 23 people were killed by adulterated wine.
