summer season which accounts for more than half of annual volume.
Mr Ottosson added that the SKr500m cost savings programme in its ailing
Sealink cross-Channel operations had now been carried out satisfactorily,
along with a wage freeze until 1993 and closure of the Folkstone-Boulogne
route. The investment plans have also been implemented in Sealink, said Mr
Ottosson. The aim now was to utilise the additional capacity, he said. For
this reason, Stena Line viewed the future in a positive light.
