<TEXT>
The Greater Nottingham Co-operative Society, one of the largest co-operative
societies still trading independently, has approached the Co-operative
Wholesale Society about a possible merger, writes John Thornhill.
Its incorporation into the CWS would confirm the trend of recent years which
has shown a marked consolidation of the co-operative movement.
The GNCS, which employs about 7,000 people, last year turned over Pounds
381.4m and made operating profits of Pounds 9.4m. It runs 113 grocery stores
and 70 non-food stores and also offers funeral, garage and travel services.
