Richard Lay, chairman. 'The second half of our financial year will not be
easy and I look beyond 1992 for the beginning of a worthwhile recovery in
our markets.'
Earnings per share came out at 1.22p against 4.11p last time, and there is a
reduced dividend of 1p (2.4p).
