FT  15 JAN 92 / Observer: Capacious
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It may soon take a head for more than numbers to work at Britain's Central
Statistical Office. Australian Bill McLennan, its new director, is known not
only for his professional skill but for his fluid approach to management.
As deputy head of the Australian Bureau of Statistics, he has become
renowned for his use of socialising to promote morale. It is said he can
outdrink most of his colleagues.
The bureau's house magazine lately reported that McLennan joined the members
of a management course for drinks which went on into the small hours. But
next day, McLennan still left the hotel 'clear of head and conscience' at
6.30 in the morning, and put in a nine-hour day before catching the 9pm
flight to Tokyo.
