FT  15 JAN 92 / British Gas decision today
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE BOARD of British Gas meets today to decide whether to submit to a
Monopolies and Mergers Commission investigation.
British Gas agreed with the Office of Fair Trading to cut its industrial
market share from 90 per cent to 40 per cent and hive off its transport
division. In return, it expects Ofgas, the industry regulator, to review a
tough formula for domestic prices which is due to come in force in April.
It must tell the OFT by tomorrow if it will go ahead with changes to the
industrial market without conditions attached or face an inquiry into its
dominance of the industrial market.
</TEXT>
