<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 92 / World News in Brief: Sports stars retire
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fatima Whitbread, 30, Britain's former world champion javelin thrower, is to
retire because of a shoulder injury. Brazilian Nelson Piquet, 39, three
times formula one world motor racing champion, is also retiring.
