<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 92 / World News in Brief: Sunday racing plan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Stewards of the Jockey Club, horse-racing's governing body, agreed in
principle to introduce Sunday racing. Betting is illegal at any track on a
Sunday, so courses will not charge admission and bookies will be unable to
operate on the track. Bets must be made through credit accounts.
