<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 92 / International Capital Markets: Bass preference offer to
stand
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BASS, the UK brewing group, intends to proceed with an offer to repay
holders of its 4 per cent preference shares less than they are formally
entitled to under its articles of association, despite objections from one
small holder.
The offer, of 57.5p a share, will only go ahead if holders agree to vary
their rights at a special meeting convened for later this month, said Ms
Gisela Gledhill, company secretary. Under Bass's articles, preference
shareholders are entitled to repayment at par - Pounds 1  - in a winding-up
or reduction in the group's capital.
The offer for the shares, which compares with a previous market price of
38p, was made after taking advice from J. Henry Schroder Wagg, the merchant
bank, and consultation with institutional holders.
